cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the problem of gender classification from face images, which is a core problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to analyze the data, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks and post-hoc explanation techniques, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with issues related to bias and fairness in machine learning, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
